%I A397074 #7 Jun 24 2026 22:09:32
%S A397074 1,2,7,125,355251
%N A397074 Number of NPN-equivalence classes of Boolean functions of n variables whose sensitivity is equal to n.
%C A397074 The sensitivity s(f) of a Boolean function f is the maximum over all inputs x of the number of coordinates i such that flipping the i-th bit of x changes the value of f. Here we count the NPN-equivalence classes (functions up to negation of input variables, permutation of input variables, and negation of the output) of n-variable Boolean functions attaining the maximum possible sensitivity, s(f) = n.
%C A397074 Block sensitivity bs(f) and certificate complexity C(f) yield the same terms: the counts of n-variable classes with bs(f) = n and with C(f) = n coincide with this sequence for n = 1..5 (1, 2, 7, 125, 355251); whether the three measures continue to agree for n >= 6 is open.
%C A397074 a(5) = 355251 was obtained from a complete census of all 616126 NPN classes of Boolean functions on at most 5 variables.
%Y A397074 Cf. A000370 (number of NPN-equivalence classes of Boolean functions of n or fewer variables), A397075 (degree), A397076 (deterministic decision-tree complexity).
%K A397074 nonn,hard,more
%O A397074 1,2
